threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a MIPS ELF malware, a variant of the Mirai botnet, designed to infect IoT devices. It contains a brute-force module (sub_40f958) with a large, hardcoded list of over 150 default credentials to spread to other devices via Telnet. The binary also functions as a downloader, constructing shell commands to fetch and execute secondary payloads using `wget`, `tftp`, and `ftpget`. The presence of the string `GET /dlr.` is a strong indicator of a Mirai dropper.
